Here is the translation:

Only devotees of Jetha Bhagwan, Koteshwar Mai; 
In this life, there is no peace, only Kuldharma will be worshiped Hari.

Here are the translated statements:

 Hari Bhakt che Havnanbai, Ehaadi Jan Aadroj Main; 
 Jeevi Ratan Ne Prabhudas, Kanbhi Bhakt Kolavade Vas.

Here is the translation:

You want to bind the one who binds, this is the beginning of understanding; 
The devotee is a sweet potter, he settles in his own village Mozar.

Devotee warriors will conquer the heart of Hari; 
Royal soldiers will conquer in war and defeat their enemies, 
and after many years of battle, they will have peace.

Here is the translation:

God's wife says, "In Gama Ithor, that very life; 
The devoted one is happy, worships Hari at Upara."

This devotion is done by the Lord's mercy; 
remaining in the village, it becomes unbearable; 
there is no living without Harikho Satawaro, 
the devout Bhakt Raychand is a true one.
